From f6b16d4dd35ed532b6c6e92f6424b085d671d016 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Claude (assistant)" <dev@example.com>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 07:35:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Restructure blog/practice-page URLs and fix site-wide SEO
 metadata per client sheet

- Add per-page meta title/description to MainLayout.astro and Hugo's
  baseof.html (previously hardcoded to <title>Website</title> with no
  meta description anywhere on the site).
- Move all 38 Hugo-rendered practice-area pages off the generic
  /blog/<slug>/ catch-all onto their client-specified URLs (e.g.
  /wills-and-probate/, /employment-law/employees/redundancies/,
  /power-of-attorney/enduring/), driven by a "url" front-matter field
  per content file.
- Reserve /blog/ for the genuine news/insights feed only; practice
  pages are excluded from that listing via "_build.list: never".
- Fix hugo.toml publishDir (was pointing at an unused leftover folder)
  and wire Hugo into the real build pipeline via npm scripts plus
  scripts/merge-hugo-output.mjs.
- Port the site header/nav/footer into Hugo layouts/partials so
  Hugo-rendered pages match the rest of the site.
- Relocate the two Figma-built pages (dispute-2, redundancy-2) to
  their real final URLs; mark the corresponding duplicate markdown
  as draft to avoid a build collision.
- Update Navbar/Footer/Topbar links across the Astro site to the new
  URLs; remove now-obsolete /blog catch-all routes and the stale
  pre-built public/blog/ snapshot.
- Add public/_redirects (301s) from old URLs to new ones.
