-      <h1 id="conveyancing-solicitor">Conveyancing Solicitor</h1>
-<h2 id="flawless-property-transactions-to-protect-your-most-valuable-asset">Flawless Property Transactions to Protect Your Most Valuable Asset</h2>
-<p>Buying or selling property should be a milestone of success, not a source of sleepless nights over title defects, planning concerns, or delayed mortgage approvals.</p>
-<p>Whether you are purchasing your first home, selling an investment property, or acquiring commercial premises, every legal detail matters.</p>
-<p>We manage your property transaction with precision and care, ensuring your interests are protected from contract to completion.</p>
-<h2 id="the-hidden-stress-of-property-transactions">The Hidden Stress of Property Transactions</h2>
-<p>Property transactions are often among the most significant financial commitments people make.</p>
-<p>You may find yourself asking:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Will a boundary dispute delay our move?</li>
-<li>Could a title issue jeopardise the transaction?</li>
-<li>What happens if the bank delays the mortgage drawdown?</li>
-<li>Are there planning or compliance issues hidden within the property records?</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Unfortunately, small legal problems can quickly become expensive complications.</p>
-<p>Without proper legal oversight, buyers and sellers may face delays, unexpected costs, or transactions that collapse at the final stage.</p>
-<p>Our role is to remove uncertainty, manage the process, and protect your investment from unnecessary risk.</p>
-<h2 id="our-property-conveyancing-services">Our Property Conveyancing Services</h2>
-<p>When your property, finances, and future plans are at stake, you need solicitors with extensive experience in Irish property law and conveyancing procedures.</p>
-<p>Our services include:</p>
-<h3 id="residential-purchases-and-sales">Residential Purchases and Sales</h3>
-<p>Managing every stage of residential transactions, including:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Family homes</li>
-<li>Investment properties</li>
-<li>Apartments</li>
-<li>High-value residential assets</li>
-</ul>
-<p>From initial contracts through to key handover, we ensure the process runs smoothly.</p>
-<h3 id="commercial-conveyancing">Commercial Conveyancing</h3>
-<p>Providing legal support for:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Office purchases</li>
-<li>Retail premises</li>
-<li>Commercial leases</li>
-<li>Investment acquisitions</li>
-<li>Business property transactions</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We ensure your commercial interests are protected throughout the transaction.</p>
-<h3 id="family-farm-and-voluntary-transfers">Family Farm and Voluntary Transfers</h3>
-<p>Assisting families with:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Agricultural land transfers</li>
-<li>Succession planning</li>
-<li>Family property transfers</li>
-<li>Tax-efficient ownership structures</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We guide clients through complex legal and taxation considerations.</p>
-<h3 id="remortgaging-and-equity-release">Remortgaging and Equity Release</h3>
-<p>Working closely with lenders to facilitate:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Refinancing arrangements</li>
-<li>Mortgage restructuring</li>
-<li>Equity release transactions</li>
-<li>Property-based lending requirements</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Our goal is to ensure funds are released efficiently and securely.</p>
-<h2 id="the-strategic-advantage-thorough-title-investigation">The Strategic Advantage: Thorough Title Investigation</h2>
-<p>Many legal issues only become visible when a property&rsquo;s history is carefully examined.</p>
-<p>At Martina Murphy Solicitors, we conduct detailed investigations before contracts are signed.</p>
-<p>Our team carefully reviews:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Title deeds</li>
-<li>Land Registry records</li>
-<li>Planning permissions</li>
-<li>Building compliance certificates</li>
-<li>Mapping documentation</li>
-<li>Rights of way</li>
-<li>Boundary issues</li>
-</ul>
-<p>If there are planning irregularities, title defects, or unresolved disputes, we identify them early and provide practical solutions.</p>
-<p>This proactive approach helps prevent expensive surprises after completion.</p>
-<h2 id="financial-clarity-no-hidden-costs">Financial Clarity: No Hidden Costs</h2>
-<p>Unexpected costs can place significant pressure on a property transaction.</p>
-<p>We provide clear, transparent advice from the outset regarding:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Legal fees</li>
-<li>Stamp Duty</li>
-<li>Land Registry charges</li>
-<li>Search fees</li>
-<li>Registration expenses</li>
-<li>Third-party costs</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Our clients receive a clear understanding of the anticipated costs involved so they can make informed decisions with confidence.</p>
-<h2 id="a-seamless-path-to-completion">A Seamless Path to Completion</h2>
-<p>Property transactions involve multiple parties, deadlines, and legal requirements.</p>
-<p>Our role is to coordinate the process efficiently and keep matters moving forward.</p>
-<h3 id="personal-legal-consultation">Personal Legal Consultation</h3>
-<p>We take the time to understand:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Your objectives</li>
-<li>The nature of the transaction</li>
-<li>Any concerns or special requirements</li>
-</ul>
-<p>This allows us to tailor our advice to your circumstances.</p>
-<h3 id="rigorous-due-diligence">Rigorous Due Diligence</h3>
-<p>We undertake comprehensive legal investigations, including:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Reviewing contracts for sale</li>
-<li>Conducting property searches</li>
-<li>Investigating title issues</li>
-<li>Liaising with lenders</li>
-<li>Coordinating with engineers and surveyors</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Every detail is carefully reviewed before commitments are made.</p>
-<h3 id="completion-and-closing">Completion and Closing</h3>
-<p>We manage:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Transfer of funds</li>
-<li>Mortgage drawdowns</li>
-<li>Execution of legal documents</li>
-<li>Property registration requirements</li>
-</ul>
-<p>allowing you to focus on your move or investment plans.</p>
-<h2 id="the-martina-murphy-difference">The Martina Murphy Difference</h2>
-<p>With over 100 years of combined legal experience, Martina Murphy Solicitors has built a reputation for professionalism, attention to detail, and exceptional client service.</p>
-<p>Clients choose us because we provide:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Clear legal advice</li>
-<li>Personal attention</li>
-<li>Thorough investigations</li>
-<li>Efficient transaction management</li>
-<li>Extensive conveyancing experience</li>
-</ul>
-<p>When you instruct our firm, you gain a dedicated legal team committed to protecting one of your most important investments.</p>
-<h2 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
-<h3 id="how-long-does-the-conveyancing-process-take-in-ireland">How long does the conveyancing process take in Ireland?</h3>
-<p>Most residential transactions complete within approximately six to eight weeks after a property becomes sale agreed.</p>
-<p>However, timelines can vary depending on factors such as:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Title complexity</li>
-<li>Mortgage approval timelines</li>
-<li>Property chain issues</li>
-<li>Additional investigations required</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We work proactively to minimise delays wherever possible.</p>
-<h3 id="what-costs-should-i-expect-when-buying-a-property">What costs should I expect when buying a property?</h3>
-<p>In addition to the purchase price, buyers should budget for:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Legal fees</li>
-<li>Stamp Duty</li>
-<li>Land Registry fees</li>
-<li>Search fees</li>
-<li>Registration costs</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We provide a clear breakdown of anticipated expenses at the outset of the transaction.</p>
-<h3 id="is-sale-agreed-legally-binding">Is &ldquo;Sale Agreed&rdquo; legally binding?</h3>
-<p>No.</p>
-<p>A property becoming sale agreed does not create a legally binding contract.</p>
-<p>Either party may withdraw from the transaction until formal contracts are signed and the necessary contractual obligations are completed.</p>
-<h3 id="do-i-need-a-structural-survey-before-buying-a-property">Do I need a structural survey before buying a property?</h3>
-<p>Yes.</p>
-<p>Under the principle of caveat emptor (&ldquo;buyer beware&rdquo;), purchasers are responsible for investigating the condition of a property.</p>
-<p>An independent structural survey can identify issues such as:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Dampness</li>
-<li>Structural movement</li>
-<li>Subsidence</li>
-<li>Roofing defects</li>
-<li>Water ingress</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We strongly recommend obtaining a professional survey before signing contracts.</p>
-<hr>
-<p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p>
-<p><em>In contentious business, a solicitor may not calculate fees or other charges as a percentage or proportion of any award or settlement.</em></p>
