-<h1 id="estate-planning">Estate Planning</h1>
-<h2 id="securing-your-wealth-and-protecting-your-familys-future">Securing Your Wealth and Protecting Your Family’s Future</h2>
-<p>Estate planning is far more than preparing a legal document. It is about ensuring that everything you have built over a lifetime—your property, savings, and business—is protected and passed on smoothly to the people you care about most.</p>
-<p>Without proper planning, your estate may face unnecessary delays, tax burdens, and disputes that can place emotional and financial strain on your family.</p>
-<p>At Martina Murphy Solicitors, we provide clear, structured, and legally robust estate planning solutions designed to protect your legacy and give you complete peace of mind.</p>
-<h2 id="the-hidden-risks-of-an-unprotected-legacy">The Hidden Risks of an Unprotected Legacy</h2>
-<p>For many individuals—particularly professionals, business owners, and parents—the future brings understandable concerns:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>What happens if I lose capacity to manage my affairs?</li>
-<li>Will my family face large tax bills on inheritance?</li>
-<li>Could my children be forced to sell assets to cover liabilities?</li>
-<li>What happens if my estate is frozen after my death?</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Without a properly structured estate plan, your assets may be distributed according to default legal rules rather than your personal wishes.</p>
-<p>This can result in unnecessary delays, higher tax exposure, and avoidable family conflict.</p>
-<p>We help remove uncertainty by creating clear, legally sound plans tailored to your unique circumstances.</p>
-<h2 id="our-estate-planning-services">Our Estate Planning Services</h2>
-<p>We provide comprehensive estate planning support designed to protect your wealth and ensure your wishes are carried out exactly as intended.</p>
-<h3 id="bespoke-wills-and-trusts">Bespoke Wills and Trusts</h3>
-<p>We draft legally robust wills and establish trusts to:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Protect minor children and dependents</li>
-<li>Safeguard vulnerable beneficiaries</li>
-<li>Ensure controlled and structured distribution of assets</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="business-succession-planning">Business Succession Planning</h3>
-<p>We help business owners structure succession arrangements to:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Ensure continuity of operations</li>
-<li>Prevent ownership disputes</li>
-<li>Facilitate smooth transfer of shares or assets</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="tax-efficient-estate-structuring">Tax-Efficient Estate Structuring</h3>
-<p>We implement strategies to legally reduce inheritance tax exposure, including:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Capital Acquisitions Tax (CAT) planning</li>
-<li>Use of available reliefs and exemptions</li>
-<li>Structuring lifetime transfers where appropriate</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="probate-and-estate-administration-planning">Probate and Estate Administration Planning</h3>
-<p>As experienced probate practitioners, we structure estates to ensure:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Faster administration after death</li>
-<li>Reduced legal costs for executors</li>
-<li>Fewer disputes during probate</li>
-</ul>
-<h2 id="the-strategic-advantage-future-protection-with-dignity">The Strategic Advantage: Future Protection with Dignity</h2>
-<p>Effective estate planning goes beyond what happens after death—it also protects you during your lifetime.</p>
-<p>We specialise in integrating long-term safeguards such as:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Enduring Powers of Attorney (EPA)</li>
-<li>Decision Support Service (DSS) compliance</li>
-<li>Healthcare and financial decision planning</li>
-</ul>
-<p>These instruments ensure that if you lose capacity due to illness or injury, trusted individuals can legally manage your affairs without court intervention.</p>
-<p>This protects your dignity, autonomy, and financial security.</p>
-<h2 id="financial-clarity-and-tax-efficient-wealth-transfer">Financial Clarity and Tax-Efficient Wealth Transfer</h2>
-<p>A well-structured estate plan ensures that your assets are transferred efficiently and with minimal tax exposure.</p>
-<p>We provide clear guidance on:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Agricultural Relief and Business Relief</li>
-<li>Family home and property planning</li>
-<li>Lifetime gifting strategies</li>
-<li>Structuring inheritances for tax efficiency</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Our approach is straightforward and practical, ensuring you understand exactly how your estate will be managed and transferred.</p>
-<h2 id="a-clear-and-structured-planning-process">A Clear and Structured Planning Process</h2>
-<p>We understand that estate planning involves important and sometimes sensitive decisions.</p>
-<p>Our process is designed to be simple, supportive, and fully transparent.</p>
-<h3 id="initial-consultation">Initial Consultation</h3>
-<p>We take the time to understand:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Your assets and financial structure</li>
-<li>Your family circumstances</li>
-<li>Your long-term wishes and priorities</li>
-<li>Any concerns about inheritance or taxation</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="estate-structuring-strategy">Estate Structuring Strategy</h3>
-<p>We design a tailored estate plan that may include:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Wills and trusts</li>
-<li>Tax planning mechanisms</li>
-<li>Business succession arrangements</li>
-<li>Capacity planning instruments</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="drafting-and-implementation">Drafting and Implementation</h3>
-<p>We prepare all legal documentation and ensure:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Full legal compliance</li>
-<li>Clear and unambiguous drafting</li>
-<li>Proper execution and witnessing</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We also provide secure storage and ongoing updates where required.</p>
-<h2 id="the-martina-murphy-difference">The Martina Murphy Difference</h2>
-<p>With over 100 years of combined legal experience, Martina Murphy Solicitors is trusted for delivering clear, practical, and highly effective estate planning solutions.</p>
-<p>Clients choose us because we provide:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Straight-talking legal advice</li>
-<li>Detailed and structured planning</li>
-<li>Strong focus on tax efficiency</li>
-<li>Deep expertise in succession and capacity law</li>
-<li>Compassionate and discreet service</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We believe estate planning should give you certainty—not complexity.</p>
-<p>Our role is to ensure your legacy is protected exactly as you intend.</p>
-<h2 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
-<h3 id="why-is-estate-planning-important">Why is estate planning important?</h3>
-<p>Estate planning ensures your assets are distributed according to your wishes and helps reduce tax exposure, legal delays, and family disputes.</p>
-<h3 id="what-happens-if-i-die-without-a-will">What happens if I die without a will?</h3>
-<p>If you die without a will, your estate will be distributed according to intestacy rules, which may not reflect your personal wishes.</p>
-<h3 id="can-estate-planning-reduce-inheritance-tax">Can estate planning reduce inheritance tax?</h3>
-<p>Yes. Proper structuring can help reduce Capital Acquisitions Tax (CAT) liability through reliefs, exemptions, and strategic planning.</p>
-<h3 id="what-is-the-difference-between-a-will-and-an-estate-plan">What is the difference between a will and an estate plan?</h3>
-<p>A will is one component of estate planning. A full estate plan may also include trusts, tax planning, business succession strategies, and capacity planning tools.</p>
