-<h1 id="family-home--property">Family Home &amp; Property</h1>
-<h2 id="securing-your-most-valuable-asset-in-a-divorce">Securing Your Most Valuable Asset in a Divorce</h2>
-<p>The family home is often the most valuable asset involved in a separation or divorce.</p>
-<p>Beyond its financial value, it represents security, stability, family memories, and, for many parents, continuity for their children.</p>
-<p>When relationships break down, questions surrounding ownership, occupation, mortgage responsibility, and future housing arrangements can quickly become complex.</p>
-<p>At Martina Murphy Solicitors, we provide practical, strategic legal advice to help clients protect their interests while working towards fair and sustainable property arrangements.</p>
-<h2 id="the-emotional-and-financial-impact-of-property-disputes">The Emotional and Financial Impact of Property Disputes</h2>
-<p>Many clients come to us with concerns such as:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Who gets the family home?</li>
-<li>Will I have to sell the property?</li>
-<li>Can my spouse force a sale?</li>
-<li>What happens if both names are on the mortgage?</li>
-<li>Can I remain in the home with the children?</li>
-<li>What if I want to buy out my spouse&rsquo;s share?</li>
-</ul>
-<p>These concerns are entirely understandable.</p>
-<p>Property issues often represent the largest financial aspect of any separation and can have long-term consequences for both parties.</p>
-<p>Our role is to provide clarity, protect your legal rights, and help secure a practical outcome that supports your future.</p>
-<h2 id="our-family-home-and-property-services">Our Family Home and Property Services</h2>
-<p>We advise clients on a wide range of property-related family law matters.</p>
-<h3 id="family-home-settlements">Family Home Settlements</h3>
-<p>We assist with:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Family home negotiations</li>
-<li>Property ownership disputes</li>
-<li>Separation agreements</li>
-<li>Judicial separation proceedings</li>
-<li>Divorce settlements</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Our goal is to achieve fair arrangements that reflect both legal rights and practical realities.</p>
-<h3 id="property-transfers-between-spouses">Property Transfers Between Spouses</h3>
-<p>Where one party wishes to retain the family home, we can assist with:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Property transfers</li>
-<li>Transfer deeds</li>
-<li>Mortgage lender requirements</li>
-<li>Refinancing arrangements</li>
-<li>Registration of ownership changes</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="property-sale-and-division-of-proceeds">Property Sale and Division of Proceeds</h3>
-<p>In some cases, selling the property may be the most practical solution.</p>
-<p>We advise on:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Sale arrangements</li>
-<li>Division of proceeds</li>
-<li>Settlement structures</li>
-<li>Tax considerations</li>
-<li>Future housing requirements</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="investment-properties-and-additional-assets">Investment Properties and Additional Assets</h3>
-<p>Many families own more than one property.</p>
-<p>We provide advice regarding:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Rental properties</li>
-<li>Holiday homes</li>
-<li>Commercial property</li>
-<li>Agricultural land</li>
-<li>International property interests</li>
-</ul>
-<h2 id="understanding-property-rights-during-divorce">Understanding Property Rights During Divorce</h2>
-<p>Every family situation is unique.</p>
-<p>Irish courts do not automatically divide assets equally.</p>
-<p>Instead, a range of factors may be considered, including:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>The needs of dependent children</li>
-<li>Financial contributions</li>
-<li>Future earning capacity</li>
-<li>Housing requirements</li>
-<li>Pension provision</li>
-<li>Overall family circumstances</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Because every case is different, obtaining tailored legal advice is essential before making decisions about property ownership or settlement proposals.</p>
-<h2 id="the-strategic-advantage-looking-beyond-the-family-home">The Strategic Advantage: Looking Beyond the Family Home</h2>
-<p>While the family home often attracts the greatest attention during negotiations, it is rarely the only asset that matters.</p>
-<p>A comprehensive review may include:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Savings accounts</li>
-<li>Investment portfolios</li>
-<li>Business interests</li>
-<li>Pension funds</li>
-<li>Company shares</li>
-<li>Overseas assets</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Understanding the complete financial picture allows more effective negotiations and often creates greater flexibility when reaching settlement agreements.</p>
-<p>Our objective is to ensure that all relevant assets are properly considered before any final agreement is reached.</p>
-<h2 id="financial-clarity-throughout-the-process">Financial Clarity Throughout the Process</h2>
-<p>Property settlements can have significant financial implications.</p>
-<p>We help clients understand issues such as:</p>
-<h3 id="mortgage-responsibility">Mortgage Responsibility</h3>
-<p>We review:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Existing mortgage obligations</li>
-<li>Refinancing options</li>
-<li>Joint liability issues</li>
-<li>Affordability considerations</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="tax-considerations">Tax Considerations</h3>
-<p>Certain property transfers between spouses may benefit from specific tax exemptions.</p>
-<p>We provide guidance regarding:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Capital Gains Tax considerations</li>
-<li>Stamp Duty implications</li>
-<li>Transfer structures</li>
-<li>Timing considerations</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="long-term-financial-planning">Long-Term Financial Planning</h3>
-<p>We help clients evaluate whether proposed arrangements are sustainable and realistic for their future financial circumstances.</p>
-<h2 id="our-process">Our Process</h2>
-<h3 id="confidential-initial-consultation">Confidential Initial Consultation</h3>
-<p>We begin by understanding:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Your family circumstances</li>
-<li>Property ownership arrangements</li>
-<li>Financial concerns</li>
-<li>Immediate priorities</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="property-and-asset-assessment">Property and Asset Assessment</h3>
-<p>We review:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Property valuations</li>
-<li>Mortgage documentation</li>
-<li>Ownership structures</li>
-<li>Financial disclosures</li>
-<li>Related assets</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="negotiation-and-resolution">Negotiation and Resolution</h3>
-<p>Where possible, we seek practical negotiated outcomes through:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Solicitor negotiations</li>
-<li>Mediation</li>
-<li>Collaborative solutions</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Where necessary, we provide strong representation through formal court proceedings.</p>
-<h3 id="property-transfer-and-completion">Property Transfer and Completion</h3>
-<p>Once an agreement is reached, we manage:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Legal documentation</li>
-<li>Conveyancing requirements</li>
-<li>Property transfers</li>
-<li>Registration processes</li>
-</ul>
-<p>This ensures the final settlement is implemented correctly and efficiently.</p>
-<h2 id="why-clients-choose-martina-murphy-solicitors">Why Clients Choose Martina Murphy Solicitors</h2>
-<p>With over 100 years of combined legal experience, we understand that property disputes during separation involve far more than financial figures.</p>
-<p>Clients trust us because we provide:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Clear legal advice</li>
-<li>Practical solutions</li>
-<li>Strategic negotiation</li>
-<li>Strong representation</li>
-<li>Compassionate support</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We are committed to helping clients move forward with confidence and security.</p>
-<h2 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
-<h3 id="who-gets-the-family-home-in-a-divorce">Who gets the family home in a divorce?</h3>
-<p>There is no automatic rule.</p>
-<p>The outcome depends on the specific circumstances of each family, including financial resources, housing needs, and the welfare of any dependent children.</p>
-<h3 id="can-my-spouse-force-the-sale-of-the-house">Can my spouse force the sale of the house?</h3>
-<p>Not necessarily.</p>
-<p>Whether a property is sold, transferred, or retained by one party depends on the overall settlement and legal circumstances.</p>
-<h3 id="can-i-buy-out-my-spouses-share-of-the-property">Can I buy out my spouse&rsquo;s share of the property?</h3>
-<p>In many cases, yes.</p>
-<p>This often involves obtaining an updated valuation and arranging mortgage refinancing where necessary.</p>
-<h3 id="what-happens-if-both-names-are-on-the-mortgage">What happens if both names are on the mortgage?</h3>
-<p>Even if one person leaves the property, both parties may remain legally responsible to the lender unless formal arrangements are made.</p>
-<h3 id="are-investment-properties-included-in-a-divorce-settlement">Are investment properties included in a divorce settlement?</h3>
-<p>Yes.</p>
-<p>All relevant assets may be considered when determining an appropriate financial settlement.</p>
-<hr>
-<p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p>
-<p><em>In contentious business, a solicitor may not calculate fees or other charges as a percentage or proportion of any award or settlement.</em></p>
