-      <h1 id="power-of-attorney-solicitors">Power of Attorney Solicitors</h1>
-<h2 id="retain-control-of-your-future-and-protect-your-familys-peace-of-mind">Retain Control of Your Future and Protect Your Family’s Peace of Mind</h2>
-<p>Planning for the future means ensuring that your financial, property, and personal affairs remain protected if you become unable to make decisions for yourself.</p>
-<p>A properly drafted Power of Attorney allows you to appoint trusted individuals to act on your behalf, providing certainty for both you and your family during challenging circumstances.</p>
-<p>At Martina Murphy Solicitors, we provide practical, compassionate, and legally robust advice on Powers of Attorney, helping clients safeguard their independence, dignity, and assets through effective future planning.</p>
-<h2 id="why-powers-of-attorney-matter">Why Powers of Attorney Matter</h2>
-<p>Many people assume that close family members automatically have authority to manage their affairs if something unexpected happens.</p>
-<p>Unfortunately, this is often not the case.</p>
-<p>Clients frequently ask:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Who will manage my finances if I become incapacitated?</li>
-<li>How can my family access important accounts if I cannot act myself?</li>
-<li>What happens if I lose mental capacity?</li>
-<li>How can I ensure my healthcare wishes are respected?</li>
-<li>How can my family avoid lengthy legal proceedings?</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Without the appropriate legal arrangements, family members may face delays, court applications, and significant stress during already difficult situations.</p>
-<p>A Power of Attorney provides clarity and protection when it is needed most.</p>
-<h2 id="our-power-of-attorney-services">Our Power of Attorney Services</h2>
-<p>We provide comprehensive future-planning solutions tailored to your individual circumstances.</p>
-<h3 id="enduring-power-of-attorney-epa">Enduring Power of Attorney (EPA)</h3>
-<p>An Enduring Power of Attorney allows you to appoint trusted individuals to make decisions on your behalf if you lose the capacity to do so in the future.</p>
-<p>An EPA may cover:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Financial affairs</li>
-<li>Property matters</li>
-<li>Personal welfare decisions</li>
-<li>Future care planning</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="ordinary-powers-of-attorney">Ordinary Powers of Attorney</h3>
-<p>An Ordinary Power of Attorney can be useful where you need someone to act on your behalf while you remain mentally capable.</p>
-<p>These arrangements are commonly used when:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Living abroad</li>
-<li>Travelling extensively</li>
-<li>Recovering from illness or surgery</li>
-<li>Managing business affairs remotely</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="advance-healthcare-directives">Advance Healthcare Directives</h3>
-<p>We assist clients with documenting their wishes regarding future medical treatment and healthcare decisions.</p>
-<p>Clear guidance can help reduce uncertainty for loved ones and healthcare professionals.</p>
-<h3 id="decision-support-service-dss-advice">Decision Support Service (DSS) Advice</h3>
-<p>The Assisted Decision-Making (Capacity) Act introduced significant reforms to future planning in Ireland.</p>
-<p>We provide guidance regarding:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>DSS registration requirements</li>
-<li>Compliance obligations</li>
-<li>Capacity planning</li>
-<li>Legal documentation</li>
-</ul>
-<h2 id="strategic-future-planning">Strategic Future Planning</h2>
-<p>A Power of Attorney should form part of a broader future-planning strategy.</p>
-<p>We assist clients with planning that protects:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Family assets</li>
-<li>Property portfolios</li>
-<li>Business interests</li>
-<li>Personal welfare</li>
-<li>Long-term financial security</li>
-</ul>
-<p>By putting the correct arrangements in place early, clients can reduce uncertainty and help ensure that their wishes are respected.</p>
-<h2 id="financial-protection-and-peace-of-mind">Financial Protection and Peace of Mind</h2>
-<p>Establishing a Power of Attorney can help avoid costly legal complications and delays if circumstances change unexpectedly.</p>
-<p>We provide practical advice regarding:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Asset protection</li>
-<li>Financial management</li>
-<li>Future incapacity planning</li>
-<li>Property administration</li>
-<li>Family security</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Our objective is to help clients retain control while creating a clear framework for trusted individuals to act when necessary.</p>
-<h2 id="our-approach">Our Approach</h2>
-<p>We understand that future-planning decisions are highly personal.</p>
-<h3 id="initial-consultation">Initial Consultation</h3>
-<p>We begin by understanding:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Your personal circumstances</li>
-<li>Your family structure</li>
-<li>Your financial affairs</li>
-<li>Your future concerns and objectives</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="tailored-legal-advice">Tailored Legal Advice</h3>
-<p>We provide clear guidance on the most appropriate arrangements for your specific situation and prepare documentation tailored to your requirements.</p>
-<h3 id="execution-and-registration">Execution and Registration</h3>
-<p>We oversee the execution process and provide guidance regarding any registration requirements, including compliance with the Decision Support Service where appropriate.</p>
-<h2 id="why-choose-martina-murphy-solicitors">Why Choose Martina Murphy Solicitors?</h2>
-<p>With over 100 years of combined legal experience, our firm has developed a reputation for providing practical legal advice with professionalism, discretion, and empathy.</p>
-<p>Clients choose us because we provide:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Clear legal guidance</li>
-<li>Personal service</li>
-<li>Future-planning expertise</li>
-<li>Complete discretion</li>
-<li>Attention to detail</li>
-<li>Long-term solutions</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We understand the importance of protecting your independence while helping your family prepare for the future with confidence.</p>
-<h2 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
-<h3 id="what-happens-if-i-lose-capacity-without-an-enduring-power-of-attorney">What happens if I lose capacity without an Enduring Power of Attorney?</h3>
-<p>Without an EPA, family members may need to apply through formal legal processes before they can manage your affairs or make certain decisions on your behalf.</p>
-<p>This can create delays, additional costs, and unnecessary stress during difficult circumstances.</p>
-<h3 id="can-i-appoint-more-than-one-attorney">Can I appoint more than one attorney?</h3>
-<p>Yes.</p>
-<p>You can appoint multiple attorneys to act jointly or jointly and severally, depending on your preferences and circumstances.</p>
-<p>We can advise on the most suitable structure for your needs.</p>
-<h3 id="does-an-ordinary-power-of-attorney-continue-if-i-lose-mental-capacity">Does an Ordinary Power of Attorney continue if I lose mental capacity?</h3>
-<p>No.</p>
-<p>An Ordinary Power of Attorney generally ceases to have effect if you lose mental capacity.</p>
-<p>An Enduring Power of Attorney is specifically designed to address future incapacity.</p>
-<h3 id="can-a-power-of-attorney-include-healthcare-decisions">Can a Power of Attorney include healthcare decisions?</h3>
-<p>Yes.</p>
-<p>Depending on the arrangements made, Powers of Attorney may work alongside Advance Healthcare Directives to help ensure your wishes are respected if you become unable to communicate them yourself.</p>
