-      <h1 id="house-purchase-solicitor">House Purchase Solicitor</h1>
-<h2 id="secure-your-dream-home-without-the-administrative-stress">Secure Your Dream Home Without the Administrative Stress</h2>
-<p>Buying a property should be a milestone of success, not a source of sleepless nights over hidden title defects, planning issues, or banking delays.</p>
-<p>A property is likely the largest financial investment you will ever make. Every legal detail matters.</p>
-<p>We execute your property purchase with absolute precision, ensuring your investment is protected and your transaction progresses smoothly from sale agreed to receiving the keys.</p>
-<h2 id="the-hidden-stress-of-securing-your-property">The Hidden Stress of Securing Your Property</h2>
-<p>For professionals, business owners, and growing families, navigating the Irish property market can be overwhelming.</p>
-<p>You may be asking yourself:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Will a boundary dispute delay our move?</li>
-<li>If the bank&rsquo;s paperwork is not perfect, could we lose our deposit?</li>
-<li>What if the property is affected by pyrite?</li>
-<li>What if an extension was built without planning permission?</li>
-<li>Are there hidden legal issues that could affect the property&rsquo;s value?</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Relying on a volume-based conveyancing service can result in costly delays, overlooked legal issues, and unnecessary risk.</p>
-<p>You do not need a processing centre. You need an experienced solicitor who will absorb the stress, manage the process, and rigorously protect your investment.</p>
-<p>We provide straightforward advice and meticulous legal oversight to ensure a secure and legally sound property purchase.</p>
-<h2 id="our-specialised-property-purchase-services">Our Specialised Property Purchase Services</h2>
-<p>When your life savings and your family&rsquo;s future home are on the line, you need experienced solicitors who understand complex title investigations, planning compliance, and mortgage requirements.</p>
-<p>Our services include:</p>
-<h3 id="residential-property-purchases">Residential Property Purchases</h3>
-<p>Managing every stage of your purchase, including:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Booking deposits</li>
-<li>Contract review</li>
-<li>Title investigation</li>
-<li>Mortgage coordination</li>
-<li>Closing and key handover</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="new-build-developments">New Build Developments</h3>
-<p>Providing legal guidance on:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Developer contracts</li>
-<li>Stage payments</li>
-<li>Building compliance documentation</li>
-<li>Snagging procedures</li>
-<li>Completion requirements</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="apartments--multi-unit-developments">Apartments &amp; Multi-Unit Developments</h3>
-<p>Reviewing:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Management company structures</li>
-<li>Service charges</li>
-<li>Sinking funds</li>
-<li>Common area obligations</li>
-<li>Financial stability of the development</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="mortgage-drawdowns">Mortgage Drawdowns</h3>
-<p>Working closely with:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Banks</li>
-<li>Mortgage brokers</li>
-<li>Financial institutions</li>
-</ul>
-<p>to ensure all lending requirements are satisfied and funds are released without delay.</p>
-<h3 id="first-time-buyer-assistance">First-Time Buyer Assistance</h3>
-<p>Advising clients on:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Help to Buy (HTB) Scheme</li>
-<li>First-Time Buyer supports</li>
-<li>Available government incentives</li>
-<li>Eligibility requirements</li>
-</ul>
-<h2 id="the-strategic-edge-protecting-your-investment-before-you-sign">The Strategic Edge: Protecting Your Investment Before You Sign</h2>
-<p>Many conveyancing firms simply process paperwork.</p>
-<p>At Martina Murphy Solicitors, we conduct a thorough investigation into the property before contracts are signed.</p>
-<p>We do not rely solely on information provided by the seller.</p>
-<p>Instead, we carefully review:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Title deeds</li>
-<li>Land Registry records</li>
-<li>Planning permissions</li>
-<li>Certificates of compliance</li>
-<li>Property maps</li>
-<li>Rights of way</li>
-<li>Boundary documentation</li>
-</ul>
-<p>If there is an unauthorised extension, mapping discrepancy, planning issue, or title defect, we identify it before it becomes your problem.</p>
-<p>This proactive approach protects both your investment and your future peace of mind.</p>
-<h2 id="financial-clarity-eliminating-hidden-costs-and-surprises">Financial Clarity: Eliminating Hidden Costs and Surprises</h2>
-<p>Unexpected costs can quickly derail a property transaction.</p>
-<p>That is why we provide complete transparency from the outset.</p>
-<p>Our team provides clear guidance on:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Stamp Duty</li>
-<li>Land Registry fees</li>
-<li>Search fees</li>
-<li>Legal costs</li>
-<li>Property registration expenses</li>
-</ul>
-<p>There are no hidden charges and no surprises at closing.</p>
-<p>By creating a structured financial roadmap from the beginning, we ensure your funds are available precisely when needed and your transaction remains on track.</p>
-<h2 id="a-seamless-path-to-getting-your-keys">A Seamless Path to Getting Your Keys</h2>
-<p>We understand that buying a home must fit around your career, family, and daily responsibilities.</p>
-<p>Our process is designed to minimise stress while maximising efficiency.</p>
-<h3 id="personal-legal-consultation">Personal Legal Consultation</h3>
-<p>We meet with our clients personally and take the time to understand their circumstances, goals, and concerns.</p>
-<h3 id="rigorous-due-diligence">Rigorous Due Diligence</h3>
-<p>Our team conducts comprehensive investigations into every aspect of the property transaction.</p>
-<p>This includes:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Reviewing contracts for sale</li>
-<li>Conducting legal searches</li>
-<li>Investigating title issues</li>
-<li>Liaising with mortgage providers</li>
-<li>Coordinating with engineers and surveyors</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="execution-and-closing">Execution and Closing</h3>
-<p>We oversee:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Mortgage drawdown</li>
-<li>Transfer of funds</li>
-<li>Completion documentation</li>
-<li>Registration requirements</li>
-</ul>
-<p>allowing you to focus on preparing for your move.</p>
-<h2 id="the-martina-murphy-difference">The Martina Murphy Difference</h2>
-<p>With over 100 years of combined legal experience, our reputation is built on professionalism, discretion, and meticulous attention to detail.</p>
-<p>We are committed to protecting our clients&rsquo; investments and ensuring every transaction is handled correctly from start to finish.</p>
-<p>Clients trust us because we provide:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Personal service</li>
-<li>Clear communication</li>
-<li>Thorough due diligence</li>
-<li>Practical legal advice</li>
-<li>Proven experience in residential conveyancing</li>
-</ul>
-<p>When you instruct Martina Murphy Solicitors, you gain a dedicated legal team committed to protecting one of the most important investments you will ever make.</p>
-<h2 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
-<h3 id="when-should-i-hire-a-house-purchase-solicitor">When should I hire a house purchase solicitor?</h3>
-<p>The ideal time is before you begin actively bidding on properties.</p>
-<p>Once a property becomes sale agreed, estate agents will immediately request your solicitor&rsquo;s details.</p>
-<p>Having your solicitor instructed early helps prevent delays and demonstrates to the seller that you are a serious and prepared buyer.</p>
-<h3 id="is-my-booking-deposit-refundable-if-the-sale-falls-through">Is my booking deposit refundable if the sale falls through?</h3>
-<p>Yes.</p>
-<p>A booking deposit is generally paid subject to contract and does not create a legally binding obligation to purchase.</p>
-<p>If legal issues arise during the transaction or mortgage approval is not obtained, the booking deposit is typically refundable.</p>
-<h3 id="what-is-a-snag-list-for-a-new-build-property">What is a snag list for a new-build property?</h3>
-<p>A snag list is a detailed inspection report prepared by an independent engineer before completion.</p>
-<p>It identifies:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Cosmetic defects</li>
-<li>Incomplete works</li>
-<li>Structural concerns</li>
-<li>Finishing issues</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We ensure appropriate contractual protections are in place so these matters can be addressed before final completion.</p>
-<h3 id="do-i-need-a-structural-survey-for-a-second-hand-property">Do I need a structural survey for a second-hand property?</h3>
-<p>Yes.</p>
-<p>Under the principle of caveat emptor (&ldquo;buyer beware&rdquo;), purchasers are responsible for investigating the physical condition of a property.</p>
-<p>A structural survey can identify significant issues such as:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Dampness</li>
-<li>Subsidence</li>
-<li>Roof defects</li>
-<li>Structural movement</li>
-<li>Water ingress</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We strongly recommend obtaining an independent engineer&rsquo;s report before signing contracts.</p>
-<hr>
-<p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p>
-<p><em>In contentious business, a solicitor may not calculate fees or other charges as a percentage or proportion of any award or settlement.</em></p>
