-<h1 id="drafting-wills">Drafting Wills</h1>
-<h2 id="preserving-your-lifes-work-and-protecting-your-family">Preserving Your Life&rsquo;s Work and Protecting Your Family</h2>
-<p>Creating a will is one of the most important steps you can take to protect your family and preserve the assets you have worked hard to build.</p>
-<p>A properly drafted will provides certainty, reduces the risk of disputes, and ensures that your wishes are respected after your death.</p>
-<p>Without a valid will, your estate may be distributed according to the rules of intestacy, which may not reflect your intentions or adequately provide for your loved ones.</p>
-<p>At Martina Murphy Solicitors, we provide clear, practical advice to help you create a legally robust estate plan that protects your family and your legacy.</p>
-<h2 id="the-risks-of-leaving-your-estate-unplanned">The Risks of Leaving Your Estate Unplanned</h2>
-<p>Many people delay making a will because it can feel uncomfortable to think about the future.</p>
-<p>However, failing to plan can create significant difficulties for those left behind.</p>
-<p>Common concerns include:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Will my spouse and children be financially secure?</li>
-<li>Who will manage my affairs if I become incapacitated?</li>
-<li>How can I protect vulnerable family members?</li>
-<li>What will happen to my business interests?</li>
-<li>Could my estate become the subject of family disputes?</li>
-</ul>
-<p>A carefully prepared will helps eliminate uncertainty and provides peace of mind for both you and your loved ones.</p>
-<h2 id="our-will-drafting-and-estate-planning-services">Our Will Drafting and Estate Planning Services</h2>
-<p>Our team provides comprehensive estate planning solutions tailored to your personal and financial circumstances.</p>
-<h3 id="bespoke-will-drafting">Bespoke Will Drafting</h3>
-<p>We prepare legally binding wills that clearly document your wishes and ensure your assets are distributed according to your intentions.</p>
-<h3 id="trusts-for-children-and-dependants">Trusts for Children and Dependants</h3>
-<p>Where appropriate, we establish trust structures designed to protect:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Minor children</li>
-<li>Vulnerable beneficiaries</li>
-<li>Dependants requiring ongoing financial support</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="business-succession-planning">Business Succession Planning</h3>
-<p>For business owners, careful succession planning is essential.</p>
-<p>We help structure arrangements that allow for the smooth transfer of:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Business ownership</li>
-<li>Shares and investments</li>
-<li>Partnership interests</li>
-<li>Commercial assets</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="international-and-cross-border-estates">International and Cross-Border Estates</h3>
-<p>We assist clients whose estates include:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Overseas property</li>
-<li>International investments</li>
-<li>Foreign bank accounts</li>
-<li>Assets located in multiple jurisdictions</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Our goal is to ensure your estate plan remains effective regardless of where assets are located.</p>
-<h2 id="the-strategic-advantage-future-planning-and-enduring-powers-of-attorney">The Strategic Advantage: Future Planning and Enduring Powers of Attorney</h2>
-<p>Effective estate planning extends beyond what happens after death.</p>
-<p>It also involves preparing for circumstances where you may no longer be able to make decisions independently.</p>
-<p>We provide guidance on:</p>
-<h3 id="enduring-powers-of-attorney-epa">Enduring Powers of Attorney (EPA)</h3>
-<p>An Enduring Power of Attorney allows you to appoint a trusted individual to make decisions on your behalf should you lose mental capacity in the future.</p>
-<h3 id="decision-support-service-dss-matters">Decision Support Service (DSS) Matters</h3>
-<p>We assist clients in understanding and implementing appropriate legal arrangements under Ireland&rsquo;s decision-support framework.</p>
-<p>These measures help protect your dignity, independence, and personal wishes while ensuring trusted individuals can act when necessary.</p>
-<h2 id="financial-clarity-and-tax-efficient-estate-planning">Financial Clarity and Tax-Efficient Estate Planning</h2>
-<p>Preserving wealth for future generations often requires careful planning.</p>
-<p>We provide practical advice regarding:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Estate structuring</li>
-<li>Beneficiary planning</li>
-<li>Capital Acquisitions Tax (CAT) considerations</li>
-<li>Family wealth preservation</li>
-<li>Asset protection strategies</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Our objective is to help ensure that as much of your estate as possible reaches your intended beneficiaries.</p>
-<h2 id="our-straightforward-will-drafting-process">Our Straightforward Will Drafting Process</h2>
-<p>We aim to make the process as simple and stress-free as possible.</p>
-<h3 id="initial-consultation">Initial Consultation</h3>
-<p>We begin by discussing:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Your family circumstances</li>
-<li>Your assets</li>
-<li>Your wishes for the future</li>
-<li>Any concerns you may have regarding estate planning</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Where necessary, we can arrange consultations that accommodate elderly or vulnerable clients.</p>
-<h3 id="estate-planning-strategy">Estate Planning Strategy</h3>
-<p>We review your financial circumstances and recommend appropriate planning structures, including wills, trusts, and powers of attorney.</p>
-<h3 id="drafting-and-execution">Drafting and Execution</h3>
-<p>Once instructions are confirmed, we prepare the necessary documentation and oversee the proper execution of your will to ensure legal validity.</p>
-<p>We can also provide secure storage arrangements for completed wills.</p>
-<h2 id="the-martina-murphy-difference">The Martina Murphy Difference</h2>
-<p>With over 100 years of combined legal experience, Martina Murphy Solicitors is committed to providing trusted legal advice with professionalism, discretion, and compassion.</p>
-<p>Clients choose us because we provide:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Personalised estate planning</li>
-<li>Clear legal advice</li>
-<li>Comprehensive future planning</li>
-<li>Tax-aware strategies</li>
-<li>Compassionate client service</li>
-<li>Long-term peace of mind</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We understand that estate planning is ultimately about protecting the people who matter most.</p>
-<h2 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
-<h3 id="why-do-i-need-a-will">Why do I need a will?</h3>
-<p>A will ensures that your assets are distributed according to your wishes and can help minimise disputes among family members after your death.</p>
-<p>Without a valid will, your estate will be distributed according to intestacy rules.</p>
-<h3 id="can-i-update-my-will-in-the-future">Can I update my will in the future?</h3>
-<p>Yes.</p>
-<p>A will should be reviewed regularly, particularly after significant life events such as:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Marriage</li>
-<li>Divorce</li>
-<li>Birth of children</li>
-<li>Acquisition of significant assets</li>
-<li>Changes in financial circumstances</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="what-is-an-enduring-power-of-attorney">What is an Enduring Power of Attorney?</h3>
-<p>An Enduring Power of Attorney allows you to appoint someone you trust to manage certain affairs if you lose the capacity to make decisions independently in the future.</p>
-<h3 id="can-i-include-business-assets-in-my-will">Can I include business assets in my will?</h3>
-<p>Yes.</p>
-<p>Business interests can form an important part of your estate plan.</p>
-<p>Proper succession planning helps ensure continuity and reduces disruption for family members, business partners, and employees.</p>
-<hr>
-<p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p>
-<p><em>In contentious business, a solicitor may not calculate fees or other charges as a percentage or proportion of any award or settlement.</em></p>
