-<h1 id="general-power-of-attorney-solicitors">General Power of Attorney Solicitors</h1>
-<h2 id="secure-your-affairs-with-legally-watertight-poa-paperwork">Secure Your Affairs with Legally Watertight POA Paperwork</h2>
-<p>Life does not stop when you are travelling, recovering from illness, managing business commitments abroad, or otherwise unavailable to handle important matters personally.</p>
-<p>A properly drafted General Power of Attorney allows someone you trust to manage specific legal, financial, or property-related matters on your behalf while ensuring your interests remain protected.</p>
-<p>At Martina Murphy Solicitors, we prepare clear, legally robust Power of Attorney documents that provide certainty, protect your assets, and ensure your affairs continue without unnecessary disruption.</p>
-<h2 id="the-risks-of-informal-arrangements">The Risks of Informal Arrangements</h2>
-<p>Many people assume that a spouse, family member, or business partner can simply step in when needed.</p>
-<p>Unfortunately, this is not how the law works.</p>
-<p>Without a valid General Power of Attorney:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Banks may refuse access to accounts</li>
-<li>Property transactions can be delayed</li>
-<li>Contracts cannot be signed on your behalf</li>
-<li>Business operations may be interrupted</li>
-<li>Important deadlines may be missed</li>
-<li>Financial decisions may be put on hold</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Verbal permission carries no legal authority.</p>
-<p>Likewise, generic online templates frequently fail to meet the standards required by financial institutions and other organisations.</p>
-<p>A professionally prepared Power of Attorney helps eliminate these risks and ensures your chosen representative can act when required.</p>
-<h2 id="our-general-power-of-attorney-services">Our General Power of Attorney Services</h2>
-<p>We provide tailored legal solutions designed around your personal, financial, and business circumstances.</p>
-<h3 id="general-power-of-attorney">General Power of Attorney</h3>
-<p>A General Power of Attorney allows a trusted individual to manage a broad range of legal and financial matters on your behalf while you remain mentally capable.</p>
-<p>This may include:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Banking transactions</li>
-<li>Managing investments</li>
-<li>Dealing with financial institutions</li>
-<li>Signing legal documents</li>
-<li>Conducting property transactions</li>
-<li>Handling administrative matters</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="limited-or-specific-powers-of-attorney">Limited or Specific Powers of Attorney</h3>
-<p>Sometimes only a single task requires delegation.</p>
-<p>We can prepare narrowly tailored documents authorising someone to:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Complete a property purchase</li>
-<li>Sign sale documentation</li>
-<li>Manage a specific bank account</li>
-<li>Execute a commercial agreement</li>
-<li>Handle a particular transaction</li>
-</ul>
-<p>This ensures your attorney has only the authority required for the specific task.</p>
-<h3 id="property-and-conveyancing-matters">Property and Conveyancing Matters</h3>
-<p>Property transactions frequently require representation when clients are overseas or unavailable.</p>
-<p>We assist with:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Property purchases</li>
-<li>Property sales</li>
-<li>Mortgage documentation</li>
-<li>Lease execution</li>
-<li>Property management arrangements</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Our documents are carefully drafted to meet the requirements of lenders, purchasers, and registration authorities.</p>
-<h3 id="business-and-corporate-matters">Business and Corporate Matters</h3>
-<p>Business owners often require continuity during periods of absence.</p>
-<p>We can prepare Powers of Attorney covering:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Commercial contracts</li>
-<li>Company administration</li>
-<li>Shareholder matters</li>
-<li>Banking arrangements</li>
-<li>Operational decision-making</li>
-</ul>
-<p>This allows your business to continue functioning smoothly while protecting your interests.</p>
-<h3 id="revocation-of-existing-powers">Revocation of Existing Powers</h3>
-<p>Where circumstances change, it may become necessary to cancel a previous Power of Attorney.</p>
-<p>We assist with:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Formal revocation documents</li>
-<li>Notification requirements</li>
-<li>Updating institutions and third parties</li>
-<li>Ensuring previous authorities are properly terminated</li>
-</ul>
-<h2 id="the-strategic-advantage-planning-beyond-today">The Strategic Advantage: Planning Beyond Today</h2>
-<p>A General Power of Attorney is an effective solution for temporary situations.</p>
-<p>However, it is important to understand its limitations.</p>
-<p>A General Power of Attorney immediately ceases to have legal effect if you lose mental capacity.</p>
-<p>This is why many clients also discuss long-term planning options such as:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Enduring Powers of Attorney (EPA)</li>
-<li>Future care planning</li>
-<li>Decision Support Service (DSS) requirements</li>
-<li>Asset protection strategies</li>
-</ul>
-<p>By considering both immediate and future needs, you can create a comprehensive legal framework that protects you and your family in every circumstance.</p>
-<h2 id="financial-clarity-and-avoiding-costly-delays">Financial Clarity and Avoiding Costly Delays</h2>
-<p>Delays in signing documents or obtaining legal authority can have significant financial consequences.</p>
-<p>A properly prepared Power of Attorney can help prevent:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Failed property transactions</li>
-<li>Delayed business decisions</li>
-<li>Frozen financial arrangements</li>
-<li>Missed contractual deadlines</li>
-<li>Unnecessary legal costs</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We provide clear, practical advice so you understand exactly how the document operates and when it can be used.</p>
-<h2 id="a-straightforward-process">A Straightforward Process</h2>
-<p>We aim to make the process efficient, practical, and stress-free.</p>
-<h3 id="initial-consultation">Initial Consultation</h3>
-<p>We discuss:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Your objectives</li>
-<li>The powers required</li>
-<li>The person you wish to appoint</li>
-<li>Any specific restrictions or conditions</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="drafting-the-document">Drafting the Document</h3>
-<p>We prepare a tailored document that clearly defines:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>The attorney&rsquo;s authority</li>
-<li>Any limitations</li>
-<li>Duration of the appointment</li>
-<li>Scope of permitted actions</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="execution-and-certification">Execution and Certification</h3>
-<p>We oversee the formal signing process and provide certified copies where required for use with banks, financial institutions, government bodies, or other organisations.</p>
-<h2 id="why-choose-martina-murphy-solicitors">Why Choose Martina Murphy Solicitors?</h2>
-<p>With over 100 years of combined legal experience, Martina Murphy Solicitors provides practical legal solutions focused on protecting clients and their interests.</p>
-<p>Clients choose us because we offer:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Clear legal advice</li>
-<li>Tailored documentation</li>
-<li>Strong attention to detail</li>
-<li>Efficient service</li>
-<li>Professional discretion</li>
-<li>Long-term planning expertise</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We believe important legal documents should be prepared properly the first time, giving you confidence and peace of mind.</p>
-<h2 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
-<h3 id="what-is-the-difference-between-a-general-power-of-attorney-and-an-enduring-power-of-attorney">What is the difference between a General Power of Attorney and an Enduring Power of Attorney?</h3>
-<p>A General Power of Attorney is used while you retain mental capacity and typically assists during periods of absence or temporary incapacity.</p>
-<p>An Enduring Power of Attorney is designed to take effect if you lose mental capacity in the future and is governed by separate legal requirements.</p>
-<h3 id="can-i-restrict-what-my-attorney-is-allowed-to-do">Can I restrict what my attorney is allowed to do?</h3>
-<p>Yes.</p>
-<p>A Power of Attorney can be drafted with very specific limitations and conditions.</p>
-<p>We regularly prepare documents that apply only to a single transaction or a narrowly defined area of responsibility.</p>
-<h3 id="will-banks-accept-online-power-of-attorney-templates">Will banks accept online Power of Attorney templates?</h3>
-<p>Many institutions have strict requirements regarding Powers of Attorney.</p>
-<p>Generic online templates may be rejected if they fail to meet legal or procedural standards.</p>
-<p>Professionally drafted documentation significantly reduces the risk of problems.</p>
-<h3 id="when-does-a-general-power-of-attorney-end">When does a General Power of Attorney end?</h3>
-<p>A General Power of Attorney typically ends when:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>You revoke it</li>
-<li>The specified expiry date is reached</li>
-<li>The authorised task is completed</li>
-<li>You lose mental capacity</li>
-<li>You pass away</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We can advise you on the most appropriate structure for your circumstances.</p>
-<hr>
-<p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p>
-<p><em>In contentious business, a solicitor may not calculate fees or other charges as a percentage or proportion of any award or settlement.</em></p>
