-<h1>Power of Attorney Solicitors</h1>
-<div>
-  <hr>
-<h1 id="power-of-attorney-solicitors">Power of Attorney Solicitors</h1>
-<h2 id="retain-control-of-your-future-and-protect-your-familys-peace-of-mind">Retain Control of Your Future and Protect Your Family’s Peace of Mind.</h2>
-<p>If the unexpected happens, ensure your financial and healthcare decisions remain in the hands of someone you explicitly trust. We provide the mature, watertight legal planning necessary to safeguard your dignity, protect your assets, and keep your family out of the courts.</p>
-<p>[Button 1: Request a Callback]
-[Button 2: Call Our Limerick Office]</p>
-<p>[Review]</p>
-<h2 id="the-heavy-burden-of-leaving-the-future-to-chance">The Heavy Burden of Leaving the Future to Chance</h2>
-<p>For established professionals and family-oriented individuals, the anxiety of losing control over personal affairs is profound.</p>
-<ul>
-<li>If I am incapacitated by a sudden illness or accident, who will access my bank accounts to pay the mortgage?</li>
-<li>If my elderly parent’s cognitive health declines, how do I legally manage their care without stripping away their dignity?</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Without a registered Power of Attorney, your spouse or children have no automatic legal authority to manage your finances or authorize healthcare. Instead, they are forced into a lengthy, highly stressful, and public court process just to pay your bills.</p>
-<p>We understand these heavy burdens. We step in to remove the guesswork, providing straight-talking, authoritative legal advice that protects your family from bureaucratic nightmares and unnecessary financial strain.</p>
-<h2 id="our-specialized-future-planning-services">Our Specialized Future Planning Services</h2>
-<p>When your autonomy is on the line, you need trusted professionals who understand complex family dynamics and the latest legislative changes. Our highly scannable, tailored services include:</p>
-<h3 id="enduring-power-of-attorney-epa">Enduring Power of Attorney (EPA)</h3>
-<p>Drafting a robust legal framework that only comes into effect if you lose the mental capacity to make decisions in the future, covering both your finances and personal welfare.</p>
-<h3 id="ordinary-power-of-attorney">Ordinary Power of Attorney</h3>
-<p>Creating temporary or specific legal authority for a trusted individual to handle your business or property affairs while you are out of the country or recovering from surgery.</p>
-<h3 id="advance-healthcare-directives">Advance Healthcare Directives</h3>
-<p>Ensuring your exact wishes regarding medical treatments and end-of-life care are legally documented and respected by medical professionals.</p>
-<h3 id="decision-support-service-dss-navigation">Decision Support Service (DSS) Navigation</h3>
-<p>Guiding families through the complexities of the modernized Assisted Decision-Making (Capacity) Act to ensure full legal compliance.</p>
-<h2 id="the-strategic-edge-expertise-in-elderly-law-and-the-dss">The Strategic Edge: Expertise in Elderly Law and the DSS</h2>
-<p>A truly strategic future plan does not just put names on a page; it ensures the document is practically enforceable when the time comes. This is where Martina Murphy Solicitors provides a profound advantage.</p>
-<p>The legal landscape in Ireland has fundamentally changed with the introduction of the Decision Support Service (DSS). An outdated or incorrectly filed EPA will be rejected. We possess deep-rooted expertise in navigating these modern frameworks.</p>
-<p>We ensure your legal instruments are structurally sound, fully compliant, and registered correctly. We handle these highly sensitive matters with the maximum dignity and respect that you, or your vulnerable family members, deserve.</p>
-<p>[CTR]</p>
-<h2 id="financial-clarity-avoiding-costly-court-interventions">Financial Clarity: Avoiding Costly Court Interventions</h2>
-<p>You have worked hard to build your financial security; our job is to ensure it is managed exactly as you intend, without being drained by avoidable legal fees.</p>
-<p>We provide absolute financial clarity on how an EPA protects your bank accounts, pensions, and property. By putting an Enduring Power of Attorney in place now, you save your family thousands of euros by avoiding the complex and stressful process of applying to the courts for a Decision-Making Representative (the modern equivalent of making someone a Ward of Court).</p>
-<p>There is no dense legalese—just straightforward, highly effective strategies that ensure your lifelong assets are utilized precisely for your care.</p>
-<h2 id="a-dignified-seamless-path-to-protection">A Dignified, Seamless Path to Protection</h2>
-<p>We know these are weighty, emotional decisions. Our approach is designed to take the administrative burden entirely off your shoulders.</p>
-<h3 id="a-private-legal-consultation">A Private Legal Consultation</h3>
-<p>We lead with empathy and a handshake. We sit down with you to understand your exact wishes. If you or an elderly relative cannot travel to our Limerick office, we will gladly come to you whether that is in the comfort of your living room, a nursing facility, or a hospital bedside.</p>
-<h3 id="designing-your-safeguards">Designing Your Safeguards</h3>
-<p>We meticulously review your assets, business interests, and family structure to draft a watertight Power of Attorney and healthcare directive tailored to your unique life.</p>
-<h3 id="execution--dss-registration">Execution &amp; DSS Registration</h3>
-<p>We draft the documents clearly and concisely, oversee the formal signing alongside necessary medical professionals, and navigate the complex registration processes to legally lock in your future.</p>
-<h2 id="why-limerick-families-trust-our-discretion">Why Limerick Families Trust Our Discretion</h2>
-<p>With over 100 years of combined legal experience, our reputation is built on absolute discretion, meticulous preparation, and proven results. We are dedicated to protecting people, not processing volume.</p>
-<p>We proudly hold the LQ Standard of Excellence because we treat our clients with genuine kindness during life’s most vulnerable planning stages, without ever compromising our legal gravitas.</p>
-<p>When you hire Martina Murphy Solicitors, you are securing your peace of mind with a firm that insists on doing it right the first time.</p>
-<p>[Testimonial]</p>
-<h2 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
-<h3 id="what-happens-if-i-lose-capacity-without-an-enduring-power-of-attorney-in-place">What happens if I lose capacity without an Enduring Power of Attorney in place?</h3>
-<p>If you lose capacity without an EPA, your family cannot automatically access your accounts or make decisions for you. They will need to apply to the Circuit Court to have a Decision-Making Representative appointed.</p>
-<p>This process is slow, emotionally taxing, and can cost thousands of euros in legal and court fees.</p>
-<h3 id="can-i-appoint-more-than-one-attorney">Can I appoint more than one attorney?</h3>
-<p>Yes. You can appoint multiple attorneys to act &ldquo;jointly&rdquo; (meaning they must agree on every decision) or &ldquo;jointly and severally&rdquo; (meaning they can make decisions independently of one another).</p>
-<p>We will provide candid advice on which structure best suits your family dynamic to avoid future deadlocks.</p>
-<h3 id="does-an-ordinary-power-of-attorney-cover-me-if-i-develop-dementia-or-have-a-severe-stroke">Does an Ordinary Power of Attorney cover me if I develop dementia or have a severe stroke?</h3>
-<p>No. An Ordinary Power of Attorney is immediately revoked the moment you lose mental capacity.</p>
-<p>To ensure someone can manage your affairs if you become incapacitated, you must specifically register an Enduring Power of Attorney (EPA).</p>
-<p>[CTR]</p>
