-      <h1 id="probate-disputes">Probate Disputes</h1>
-<h2 id="resolving-family-conflicts-with-clarity-and-gravitas">Resolving Family Conflicts with Clarity and Gravitas</h2>
-<p>When a loved one passes away, the grieving process is difficult enough without the added strain of a legal dispute over their estate.</p>
-<p>Probate disputes can create significant emotional stress, damage family relationships, and place valuable assets at risk.</p>
-<p>Whether you are an executor defending a will, a beneficiary seeking answers, or a family member concerned about the administration of an estate, you need experienced legal guidance and clear advice.</p>
-<p>At Martina Murphy Solicitors, we provide practical, strategic representation designed to protect your rights while working toward an efficient resolution.</p>
-<h2 id="the-emotional-and-financial-toll-of-probate-disputes">The Emotional and Financial Toll of Probate Disputes</h2>
-<p>For many families, probate litigation is about far more than money.</p>
-<p>Questions often arise such as:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Was my loved one influenced into changing their will?</li>
-<li>Did they fully understand the document they signed?</li>
-<li>Is the estate being administered properly?</li>
-<li>Have assets been overlooked or mismanaged?</li>
-<li>Am I receiving the inheritance I am legally entitled to?</li>
-</ul>
-<p>These concerns can create significant anxiety during an already difficult time.</p>
-<p>We provide straightforward legal advice that helps clients understand their position, assess their options, and move forward with confidence.</p>
-<h2 id="our-specialised-probate-dispute-services">Our Specialised Probate Dispute Services</h2>
-<p>Our solicitors provide representation across a wide range of contested probate and inheritance matters.</p>
-<h3 id="challenging-the-validity-of-a-will">Challenging the Validity of a Will</h3>
-<p>We advise clients regarding claims involving:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Undue influence</li>
-<li>Fraud</li>
-<li>Lack of testamentary capacity</li>
-<li>Improper execution of a will</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="section-117-applications">Section 117 Applications</h3>
-<p>Representing children who believe adequate provision was not made for them from a parent&rsquo;s estate.</p>
-<h3 id="executor-and-estate-administration-disputes">Executor and Estate Administration Disputes</h3>
-<p>Advising on issues involving:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Delays in administration</li>
-<li>Mismanagement of assets</li>
-<li>Breaches of fiduciary duty</li>
-<li>Applications concerning executors</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="spousal-and-cohabitant-rights">Spousal and Cohabitant Rights</h3>
-<p>Helping spouses, civil partners, and qualifying cohabitants protect their legal entitlements under Irish succession law.</p>
-<h3 id="proprietary-estoppel-and-inheritance-promises">Proprietary Estoppel and Inheritance Promises</h3>
-<p>Representing individuals who relied upon promises regarding inheritance, property, family businesses, or farming assets.</p>
-<h2 id="the-strategic-advantage-uncovering-the-full-picture">The Strategic Advantage: Uncovering the Full Picture</h2>
-<p>Successful probate disputes depend upon strong evidence and careful preparation.</p>
-<p>Our team conducts detailed investigations into the circumstances surrounding the estate and any disputed issues.</p>
-<p>This may include reviewing:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Medical records</li>
-<li>Financial documentation</li>
-<li>Estate records</li>
-<li>Property transactions</li>
-<li>Witness evidence</li>
-<li>Correspondence and communications</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Our objective is to establish a clear factual picture and develop a legal strategy supported by evidence.</p>
-<h2 id="financial-clarity-and-protecting-the-estate">Financial Clarity and Protecting the Estate</h2>
-<p>Probate litigation can be costly if not managed effectively.</p>
-<p>We provide realistic and transparent advice regarding:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>The strengths and weaknesses of a case</li>
-<li>Potential legal costs</li>
-<li>Available options for resolution</li>
-<li>Risks associated with litigation</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Where appropriate, we encourage the use of:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Mediation</li>
-<li>Alternative dispute resolution</li>
-<li>Negotiated settlements</li>
-</ul>
-<p>These approaches can often reduce costs, preserve family relationships, and achieve practical outcomes more efficiently than court proceedings.</p>
-<p>When litigation becomes necessary, we provide robust representation at every stage.</p>
-<h2 id="a-clear-path-to-resolution">A Clear Path to Resolution</h2>
-<p>We understand that probate disputes often arise during periods of grief, uncertainty, and emotional strain.</p>
-<p>Our process is designed to provide clarity and reassurance throughout the matter.</p>
-<h3 id="confidential-initial-consultation">Confidential Initial Consultation</h3>
-<p>We begin by understanding:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>The family circumstances</li>
-<li>The nature of the dispute</li>
-<li>The relevant estate issues</li>
-<li>Your objectives and concerns</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="evidence-review-and-case-preparation">Evidence Review and Case Preparation</h3>
-<p>Our team carefully examines:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>The will</li>
-<li>Estate documentation</li>
-<li>Medical evidence</li>
-<li>Financial records</li>
-<li>Relevant legal issues</li>
-</ul>
-<p>to build a comprehensive strategy.</p>
-<h3 id="negotiation-and-representation">Negotiation and Representation</h3>
-<p>We manage communications with:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Executors</li>
-<li>Beneficiaries</li>
-<li>Opposing solicitors</li>
-<li>Financial institutions</li>
-<li>Relevant third parties</li>
-</ul>
-<p>while pursuing the most effective route toward resolution.</p>
-<h2 id="why-families-trust-martina-murphy-solicitors">Why Families Trust Martina Murphy Solicitors</h2>
-<p>With over 100 years of combined legal experience, Martina Murphy Solicitors has built a reputation for:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Professional excellence</li>
-<li>Careful preparation</li>
-<li>Absolute discretion</li>
-<li>Compassionate client service</li>
-<li>Strong legal advocacy</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We understand the sensitive nature of probate disputes and remain committed to protecting our clients&rsquo; interests while handling matters with professionalism and respect.</p>
-<p>When you instruct Martina Murphy Solicitors, you gain a trusted legal team dedicated to protecting your rights and your family&rsquo;s legacy.</p>
-<h2 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
-<h3 id="can-a-will-be-challenged-in-ireland">Can a will be challenged in Ireland?</h3>
-<p>Yes.</p>
-<p>A will may be challenged in certain circumstances, including allegations of:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Undue influence</li>
-<li>Lack of capacity</li>
-<li>Fraud</li>
-<li>Improper execution</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Each case depends on its specific facts and evidence.</p>
-<h3 id="what-is-a-section-117-application">What is a Section 117 application?</h3>
-<p>A Section 117 application allows a child to ask the court to consider whether a parent failed in their moral duty to make proper provision for them through their estate.</p>
-<p>Specific legal requirements and time limits apply.</p>
-<h3 id="can-an-executor-be-removed">Can an executor be removed?</h3>
-<p>In certain circumstances, the court may intervene where an executor is unable or unwilling to properly administer an estate.</p>
-<p>Applications of this nature require careful legal assessment.</p>
-<h3 id="are-probate-disputes-always-resolved-in-court">Are probate disputes always resolved in court?</h3>
-<p>No.</p>
-<p>Many probate disputes are resolved through negotiation, mediation, or other forms of alternative dispute resolution without the need for a full court hearing.</p>
-<h3 id="how-quickly-should-i-seek-legal-advice">How quickly should I seek legal advice?</h3>
-<p>Probate disputes often involve strict legal deadlines.</p>
-<p>Seeking legal advice as early as possible helps preserve evidence and ensures your rights are protected.</p>
