-      <h1 id="proven-solicitors-for-selling-a-property">Proven Solicitors for Selling a Property</h1>
-<h2 id="maximise-your-return-without-the-administrative-stress">Maximise Your Return Without the Administrative Stress</h2>
-<p>Selling a property should represent an exciting transition to the next stage of your life, not a source of unnecessary stress and uncertainty.</p>
-<p>Whether you are moving home, downsizing, relocating, or selling an investment property, the legal process must be handled efficiently and correctly.</p>
-<p>At Martina Murphy Solicitors, we provide practical, straightforward advice and meticulous legal support to help ensure your property sale progresses smoothly from instruction through to completion.</p>
-<h2 id="the-hidden-challenges-of-selling-a-property">The Hidden Challenges of Selling a Property</h2>
-<p>Many property owners underestimate the legal and administrative complexities involved in a sale.</p>
-<p>Common concerns include:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Will missing documents delay the transaction?</li>
-<li>Could planning issues affect the sale?</li>
-<li>How long will it take to receive my sale proceeds?</li>
-<li>What legal costs should I expect?</li>
-<li>What happens if the buyer raises unexpected title queries?</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Delays can cause frustration for all parties and, in some cases, place the transaction at risk.</p>
-<p>Our role is to identify potential issues early and keep your sale moving forward efficiently.</p>
-<h2 id="our-comprehensive-property-sale-services">Our Comprehensive Property Sale Services</h2>
-<p>When a significant financial asset is involved, you need experienced solicitors who understand every aspect of the conveyancing process.</p>
-<p>Our services include:</p>
-<h3 id="residential-property-sales">Residential Property Sales</h3>
-<p>Representing clients selling:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Family homes</li>
-<li>Apartments</li>
-<li>New-build properties</li>
-<li>Residential investment properties</li>
-<li>High-value private residences</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="investment-and-rental-property-sales">Investment and Rental Property Sales</h3>
-<p>Providing guidance on matters including:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Existing tenancies</li>
-<li>Capital Gains Tax considerations</li>
-<li>Sale of investment portfolios</li>
-<li>Property-related compliance issues</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="agricultural-land-and-farm-sales">Agricultural Land and Farm Sales</h3>
-<p>Assisting with:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Agricultural land transfers</li>
-<li>Farm sales</li>
-<li>Rights of way</li>
-<li>Boundary matters</li>
-<li>Mapping and registration issues</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="mortgage-and-negative-equity-transactions">Mortgage and Negative Equity Transactions</h3>
-<p>Working with lenders regarding:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Redemption figures</li>
-<li>Mortgage releases</li>
-<li>Title deed retrieval</li>
-<li>Complex lending arrangements</li>
-</ul>
-<h2 id="the-strategic-advantage-early-title-investigation">The Strategic Advantage: Early Title Investigation</h2>
-<p>One of the most common causes of delays during property sales is the late discovery of title or planning issues.</p>
-<p>At Martina Murphy Solicitors, we take a proactive approach.</p>
-<p>As soon as we are instructed, we begin reviewing:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Title deeds</li>
-<li>Land Registry records</li>
-<li>Planning documentation</li>
-<li>Property maps</li>
-<li>Relevant certificates</li>
-</ul>
-<p>This allows us to identify and address issues before contracts are issued, helping to reduce delays and avoid last-minute complications.</p>
-<h2 id="financial-clarity-from-day-one">Financial Clarity from Day One</h2>
-<p>We understand that clients want certainty regarding legal costs.</p>
-<p>That is why we provide transparent information regarding:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Professional legal fees</li>
-<li>Land Registry charges</li>
-<li>Search fees</li>
-<li>Administrative outlays</li>
-<li>Any anticipated third-party costs</li>
-</ul>
-<p>Our objective is to ensure that you understand the legal costs associated with your sale from the outset.</p>
-<p>No hidden charges.</p>
-<p>No unexpected surprises.</p>
-<p>Just clear and practical advice.</p>
-<h2 id="a-smooth-path-to-completion">A Smooth Path to Completion</h2>
-<p>We know that selling a property often takes place alongside major life changes and important financial decisions.</p>
-<p>Our process is designed to minimise stress and keep you informed throughout the transaction.</p>
-<h3 id="initial-consultation">Initial Consultation</h3>
-<p>We discuss:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Your property</li>
-<li>Your timeline</li>
-<li>Existing mortgages</li>
-<li>Any known title or planning issues</li>
-<li>Your objectives for the sale</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="pre-sale-preparation">Pre-Sale Preparation</h3>
-<p>We begin preparing the transaction by:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Requesting title deeds</li>
-<li>Reviewing title documentation</li>
-<li>Drafting contracts</li>
-<li>Identifying any legal issues requiring attention</li>
-</ul>
-<h3 id="managing-the-sale">Managing the Sale</h3>
-<p>We handle communications with:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Purchasers&rsquo; solicitors</li>
-<li>Mortgage lenders</li>
-<li>Estate agents</li>
-<li>Relevant third parties</li>
-</ul>
-<p>while progressing the transaction toward completion.</p>
-<h3 id="completion-and-transfer-of-funds">Completion and Transfer of Funds</h3>
-<p>Once the sale completes, we:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Receive sale proceeds</li>
-<li>Redeem any outstanding mortgage</li>
-<li>Finalise the legal transfer</li>
-<li>Arrange payment of net sale funds to you</li>
-</ul>
-<h2 id="why-property-sellers-choose-martina-murphy-solicitors">Why Property Sellers Choose Martina Murphy Solicitors</h2>
-<p>With over 100 years of combined legal experience, our firm has built a reputation for:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Attention to detail</li>
-<li>Clear communication</li>
-<li>Professional excellence</li>
-<li>Efficient transaction management</li>
-<li>Exceptional client service</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We understand that property transactions involve significant financial and personal considerations.</p>
-<p>Our team remains committed to protecting your interests throughout every stage of the sale.</p>
-<p>When you instruct Martina Murphy Solicitors, you gain trusted legal advisors focused on achieving a smooth, secure, and successful transaction.</p>
-<h2 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
-<h3 id="when-should-i-instruct-a-solicitor-when-selling-a-property">When should I instruct a solicitor when selling a property?</h3>
-<p>Ideally, you should instruct a solicitor before placing the property on the market.</p>
-<p>Early preparation allows title documents to be reviewed and potential issues to be identified before a buyer is found.</p>
-<h3 id="how-are-solicitor-fees-for-selling-a-property-calculated">How are solicitor fees for selling a property calculated?</h3>
-<p>Costs generally include:</p>
-<ul>
-<li>Professional legal fees</li>
-<li>Land Registry fees</li>
-<li>Search fees</li>
-<li>Administrative outlays</li>
-</ul>
-<p>We provide clear information regarding anticipated costs at the beginning of the transaction.</p>
-<h3 id="can-i-sell-a-property-if-i-cannot-locate-the-title-deeds">Can I sell a property if I cannot locate the title deeds?</h3>
-<p>In many cases, yes.</p>
-<p>The appropriate solution depends on whether the property is mortgaged and whether the title is registered.</p>
-<p>We can advise on the steps required to establish ownership and proceed with the sale.</p>
-<h3 id="what-happens-to-my-mortgage-when-the-property-is-sold">What happens to my mortgage when the property is sold?</h3>
-<p>Upon completion, any outstanding mortgage is normally redeemed from the sale proceeds before the remaining balance is transferred to you.</p>
-<p>We coordinate directly with your lender to ensure this process is completed correctly.</p>
-<hr>
-<p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p>
-<p><em>This content is provided for general information purposes only and does not constitute legal advice. Specific legal advice should always be obtained based on your individual circumstances.</em></p>
